<h1>Uses</h1>

<p>A running list of tools and gear I use daily. Inspired by <a href="https://uses.tech">uses.tech</a>.</p>

<h2>Hardware</h2>

<p><strong>MacBook Pro 14" M3</strong> — main machine. Fast enough that I stopped thinking about performance.</p>
<p><strong>LG 27" 4K monitor</strong> — one external display, centered. I stopped using two monitors and never looked back.</p>
<p><strong>Sony WH-1000XM5</strong> — noise cancelling headphones for deep work.</p>

<h2>Editor &amp; Terminal</h2>

<p><strong>Neovim</strong> — primary editor. Took a month to set up properly, saves an hour a day.</p>
<p><strong>Ghostty</strong> — terminal. Fast, native, no configuration needed to look good.</p>
<p><strong>tmux</strong> — session management. One session per project.</p>

<h2>Software</h2>

<p><strong>Arc</strong> — browser. Spaces keep client work and personal browsing separate.</p>
<p><strong>Linear</strong> — issue tracking for solo projects. Overkill but I like the keyboard shortcuts.</p>
<p><strong>Obsidian</strong> — notes and writing drafts before they become essays here.</p>
<p><strong>Postico</strong> — database GUI for when SQL in the terminal isn't enough.</p>

<h2>Stack</h2>

<p>Ruby on Rails, SQLite in production, deployed on a single Hetzner VPS via Kamal. This site is built the same way.</p>
